                    <comment id="12562674" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2008 21:04:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I should amend the Template item.  They are not useless, but I am not exactly sure how to incorporate them.  From what I can understand, they are used for transclusion (Wikipedia&apos;s term) in other documents.  Something like an import statement, if you will.  They can thus be reused across many articles.  So, technically, in order to properly index, one should resolve all the transclusions first, then index.  This doesn&apos;t seem worthwhile to do from a parsing standpoint.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12563542" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2008 15:00:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch fixes the redirect problem and the adds an option to discard image only documents (default is to keep them).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It does not strip the template pages, nor does it expand them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch applies from contrib/benchmark&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12564072" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2008 16:16:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This version alters the ExtractWikipedia class to use the EnwikiDocMaker, such that we don&apos;t have to maintain two doc producers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Doesn&apos;t do templates or pending deletions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12564085" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 30 Jan 2008 16:36:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;catch the no more data exception in ExtractWikipedia&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
